---
import UseCase from '../../../UseCase.astro';
import UseCaseInteractive from '../../../UseCaseInteractive.astro';
import Usage from '../../../Usage.astro';
import UsageItem from '../../../UsageItem.astro';
---

<UseCase
  title="Escalation to Human Judgment in Edge Cases"
  description="When the AI is uncertain, encounters edge cases, or reaches its limits, escalate to human decision-makers rather than guessing or proceeding with low confidence."
>
  <UseCaseInteractive clsHeight={112} label="Escalation in edge cases" toggle>
    <div class="grid gap-600 w-full">
      <div class="grid gap-400 p-600 rounded-lg bg-tone-neutral-09 border border-tone-neutral-03">
        <div class="grid gap-200">
          <mds-text typography="label"><b>Uncertainty Escalation</b></mds-text>
          <mds-text typography="body"
            >I'm not confident about this recommendation because the input is unusual. [Request
            human review] [Proceed anyway]</mds-text
          >
          <mds-text typography="caption" class="text-tone-neutral-05"
            >When confidence is low, the system escalates rather than proceeding with uncertainty.</mds-text
          >
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="grid gap-400 p-600 rounded-lg bg-tone-neutral-09 border border-tone-neutral-03">
        <div class="grid gap-200">
          <mds-text typography="label"><b>Edge Case Detection</b></mds-text>
          <mds-text typography="body"
            >This case falls outside our standard scenarios. [Escalate to human expert] [See why
            this needs review]</mds-text
          >
          <mds-text typography="caption" class="text-tone-neutral-05"
            >The system recognizes when it's outside its designed scope and escalates appropriately.</mds-text
          >
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="grid gap-400 p-600 rounded-lg bg-status-error-10 border border-status-error-03">
        <div class="grid gap-200">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-200">
            <mds-icon name="mi/outline/error" class="text-status-error-05"></mds-icon>
            <mds-text typography="label"
              ><b>Proceeding Despite Uncertainty (Problematic)</b></mds-text
            >
          </div>
          <mds-text typography="body"
            >AI proceeds with low-confidence recommendations or edge cases without escalating. Users
            discover problems later when the output is wrong or inappropriate.</mds-text
          >
          <mds-text typography="caption" class="text-status-error-06"
            >Errors propagate because the system doesn't recognize when to ask for help; users lose
            trust when the AI guesses incorrectly.</mds-text
          >
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </UseCaseInteractive>
  <Usage>
    <UsageItem variant="do">
      When confidence is low or cases are edge/unusual, escalate to human review rather than
      proceeding with uncertainty.
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="dont">
      Proceed automatically with low-confidence outputs or edge cases without offering escalation.
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="do">
      Explain why escalation is needed (e.g. "unusual input", "outside standard scenarios") so users
      understand the reason.
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="dont">
      Hide uncertainty or proceed as if confident when the system is actually uncertain or outside
      its scope.
    </UsageItem>
  </Usage>
</UseCase>
